To install vimscripts use the shell script 'install.sh' like so:

	./install.sh {options}

Where options are the following:

	-a

		Set 'which' to ALL.

	-p <vimpath>

		Set the path where the syntax and ftdetect folders should be
		found.

	-t

		Run vim on the specified 'which' test file.

	-w <which>

		Set which language to install, if ALL is specified, all
		languages will be installed.
